description:
Displays several units of energy consumption for households, businesses, and industries in the City of Chicago during 2010. Electric  The data was aggregated from ComEd and Peoples Natural Gas by Accenture. Electrical and gas usage data comprises 88 percent of Chicago's buildings in 2010. The electricity data comprises 68 percent of overall electrical usage in the city while gas data comprises 81 percent of all gas consumption in Chicago for 2010.

Census blocks with less than 4 accounts is displayed at the Community Area without further geographic identifiers. This dataset also contains selected variables describing selected characteristics of the Census block population, physical housing, and occupancy.
name: Energy Usage 2010

columns.name: CENSUS BLOCK
columns.description:
Census Block number obtained in the address matching/geocoding algorithms.

Blank Census Blocks correspond to data that was aggregated to the Community Area due to privacy issues.

columns.name: BUILDING TYPE
columns.description:
Building Type: Residential, Commercial, Industrial.

Blank data corresponds to blank Census Blocks.

columns.name: BUILDING_SUBTYPE
columns.description:
Building Sub-Type (6):  Single Family, Multi <7, Multi 7+, Commercial, Industrial, Municipal.

Blank cells correspond to blank Census Blocks.

columns.name: ELECTRICITY ACCOUNTS
columns.description: Number of accounts with kilowatt hour information from ComEd. An account does not equate to buildings.

columns.name: ZERO KWH ACCOUNTS
columns.description: Number of accounts with 0 kilowatt hours amounts for 12 months in 2010 from ComEd.

columns.name: GAS ACCOUNTS
columns.description: Number of accounts with THERM information from the Peoples Account and Usage files in 2010. Accounts does not equate to buildings.

columns.name: KWH TOTAL SQFT
columns.description: Total square footage associated with the electric energy usage in 2010 according to Cook County Assessor Records.

columns.name: THERMS TOTAL SQFT
columns.description: Total square footage associated with the natural gas energy usage for Kilowatt Hours in 2010 according to Cook County Assessor Records.

columns.name: KWH SQFT MEAN 2010
columns.description: Average kWh per square foot in 2010.

columns.name: THERMS SQFT MEAN 2010
columns.description: Average Therms per square foot in 2010.

columns.name: TOTAL POPULATION
columns.description: Total population from Census 2010 report (QT-P6) Race alone or in combination and Hispanic or Latino 2010.

columns.name: TOTAL UNITS
columns.description: Total number of housing units from census 2010 report (H1) Occupancy Status.

columns.name: AVERAGE STORIES
columns.description: Average number of stories based on data from Cook County Assessor's Office.

columns.name: AVERAGE BUILDING AGE
columns.description: Average Age of the buildings based on data from Cook County Assessor's Office.

columns.name: AVERAGE HOUSESIZE
columns.description: Average household size from Census 2010 report QT-P11 Households and Families.

columns.name: OCCUPIED UNITS
columns.description: Number of housing units that are occupied from census 2010 report (H1) Occupancy Status.

columns.name: RENTER-OCCUPIED HOUSING UNITS
columns.description: Number of housing units that are renter occupied from Census 2010 report (QT-H2) Tenure, Household Size and Age of Householder.

columns.name: RENTER-OCCUPIED HOUSING PERCENTAGE
columns.description: Percentage of occupied housing units that are renters from Census report (QT-H2) Tenure, Household Size and Age of Householder

columns.name: OCCUPIED HOUSING UNITS
columns.description: Number of occupied housing units from Census 2010 report (QT-H2) Tenure, Household Size and Age of Householder.
